      <scopecontent id="aspace_b12fd449cc17a32cbcfc3681a5ba36a8">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of correspondence, memoranda, and printed material relating to the Ulysses S. Grant Scholarship Foundation. The foundation, a privately run, non-profit organization, was founded in the early 1950s by Eugene Van Voorhis, a Yale freshman. Its goal was to provide tutoring by Yale student volunteers to African-American males in New Haven public schools in preparation for admission to private schools. These papers were compiled by Lerner during his tenure as a guidance counselor in the New Haven public school system.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
